## 12. Naming Conventions

| Kind                    | Convention              | Example                                   |
|-------------------------|-------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Component file          | `PascalCase.tsx`        | `EditorialImage.tsx`                      |
| Component folder        | `PascalCase/`           | `DriftChapter/`                           |
| Chapter folder          | `PascalCaseChapter/`    | `DriftChapter/`                           |
| Scene file              | `Scene<NN>_Name.tsx`    | `Scene02_Detail.tsx`                      |
| Hook file               | `useCamelCase.ts`       | `useScrollProgress.ts`                    |
| Lib utility             | `camelCase.ts`          | `lenisGsapBridge.ts`                      |
| Shader file             | `kebab-case.{frag,vert,glsl}` | `fog.frag`, `image.vert`            |
| MDX content             | `kebab-case.mdx` or `content.mdx` | `content.mdx`                  |
| Type file               | `camelCase.ts`          | `chapter.ts`                              |
| Token file              | `camelCase.ts`          | `typography.ts`                           |
| Image asset             | `kebab-case` with chapter prefix | `drift-scene02-foglake.avif`     |
| Texture asset           | `kebab-case-<size>.png` | `grain-1024.png`                          |

### Constraints
- No abbreviations (`btn`, `img`, `nav`). Spell it out.
- No generic names (`Component.tsx`, `helpers.ts`, `utils.ts` at file level вЂ” always be specific).
- `index.ts` only as folder barrel вЂ” never as actual logic file.

