## 13. Imports & Path Aliases

```jsonc
// tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./*"],
      "@app/*": ["./app/*"],
      "@components/*": ["./components/*"],
      "@lib/*": ["./lib/*"],
      "@hooks/*": ["./hooks/*"],
      "@content/*": ["./content/*"],
      "@shaders/*": ["./shaders/*"],
      "@styles/*": ["./styles/*"],
      "@types/*": ["./types/*"],
      "@public/*": ["./public/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Constraints
- Always use `@` aliases in source files. Never relative `../../../`.
- Within a folder, relative imports are fine (`./scenes/Scene02`).

